import React, { useState } from 'react' import './Calculator.css' const Calculator = () => { let[search,setsearch]=useState() return (
setsearch(e.target.value)} id="result" />
setsearch(e.target.value)} value="1" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="2" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="3" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} type="button" value="/" />
setsearch(e.target.value)} value="4" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="5" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="6" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="*" />
setsearch(e.target.value)} value="7" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="8" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="9" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="-" />
setsearch(e.target.value)} value="0" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="." /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="=" /> setsearch(e.target.value)} value="+" />
); } export default Calculator
